---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import FaqItem from '../components/FaqItem.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQs | Michael Paws"
  description="Frequently asked questions about our puppies and our breeding practices at Michael Paws."
  keywords="puppy faq, puppy questions, breeder FAQ"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subtitle="Find answers to common questions about our puppies and process"
  />

  <section class="faq-content">
    <div class="content-container">
      <h2>General Questions</h2>

      <FaqItem question="Are Staffordshire Bull Terriers a good breed?">
        <p>Staffordshire Bull Terriers are affectionate and playful dogs that make wonderful companions. They are loyal, intelligent, and full of personality. With proper training and socialization, they make excellent family pets.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Are Staffies good for beginners?">
        <p>Yes! Staffordshire Bull Terriers are great dogs for first-time dog owners. They are affectionate, relatively easy to care for, and eager to please. Their sturdy build and adaptable nature make them manageable, and they adapt well to various living situations.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do Staffies make good family pets?">
        <p>Absolutely! Not only are Staffies amazing companions, but they are also great family pets. They tend to get along well with other pets and are generally good with children, especially when properly socialized from a young age. They are often called the "nanny dog" due to their gentle nature with kids.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do Staffies smell bad?">
        <p>With proper grooming and care, your Staffie will not have a foul smell. Regular bathing, ear cleaning, and dental care are important. Consider taking your dog to a professional groomer periodically and always use quality dog shampoos.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What should I know about Staffie health?">
        <p>Staffordshire Bull Terriers are generally a robust and healthy breed. However, they can be prone to certain conditions like hip dysplasia, L-2 HGA, and hereditary cataracts. Regular vet checkups, a healthy diet, and proper exercise will help keep your Staffie in great shape.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <h2>About Our Puppies</h2>

      <FaqItem question="What is included when I purchase a puppy?">
        <p>Each puppy comes with: current vaccinations, deworming records, a veterinary health certificate, a lifetime health guarantee, a puppy starter kit, and ongoing support from our team.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="How do I reserve a puppy?">
        <p>Contact us through our website or by phone to express your interest. We'll discuss available puppies, answer your questions, and guide you through the reservation process, which typically includes a deposit.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Do you offer delivery?">
        <p>Yes! We offer both pickup and delivery options. We prefer in-person pickup so we can meet you and ensure a smooth transition, but we understand this isn't always possible. Delivery arrangements can be made across the United States.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="Are your puppies potty trained?">
        <p>We begin potty training and crate training with our puppies before they go to their new homes. While they won't be fully trained, they'll have a good foundation for you to continue their training.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <FaqItem question="What colors/patterns do you have?">
        <p>We breed a variety of beautiful colors and patterns including red, fawn, white, black, blue, brindle, and more. Check our Available Puppies page to see current options, or contact us about upcoming litters.</p>
      </FaqItem>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Have More Questions?</h3>
        <p>We're here to help! Reach out to us with any additional questions.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .faq-content {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #f8f6f3;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2a2a2a;
    margin: 2rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1B2A4A, #1B2A4A);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    color: white;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #1B2A4A;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: #2E8B8B;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-content {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
